body: onnx.checker.check_model doesn't run shape and type inference. The error says: one of the input has wrong type.

Okay, good to know @snnn. Thanks. 
(And yes, I realize it's a type error, but I'm not sure how to resolve it.)

Curious, @snnn, when I look at the GitHub docs for `Equal` it appears to accept floats. However, when I click the "?" in Netron, the documentation for the `Equal` node indicates only integer types. The latter would explain the error. Do you know how I might go about changing the type?

What opset is the model using? Opset 11 added support for float and other types, but the older opset 7 version only supported integer types. The opset version is shown in the "imports" section of the model properties of Netron.

The info in Model Properties is: `ONNX v4, Pytorch 1.3, ai.onnx v9`.
I've viewing this on macOS, but the PyTorch model and ONNX conversion are done on Ubuntu 18.04.
So, your model asks for opset 9, not 11. In opset 9, the op doesn't support float.

Yes, that seems pretty clear! ;-) 
How do I rectify the situation though? `pip install --upgrade onnx` indicates I'm up-to-date.... or is it a PyTorch upgrade?
It need be fixed in PyTorch side.
Can you try Pytorch 1.4? If resolved, please close this issue; if not, let us know and we can help look into PT export. CC @spandantiwari as fyi

Training in Pytorch 1.4 (cuda 10.1) and specifying `opset_version=11` in my conversion script allows the model to build and verify correctly under `onnxruntime`. However, the converted model reports Pytorch 1.3 (in Netron)... ?? Also, when using Opset v11, the resulting model contains a `Range` function, which fails on `onnx-coreml` conversion with: `NotImplementedError: Unsupported ONNX ops of type: Range`. Strange.

Do you know which onnx opset is supported by the latest onnx-coreml converter ? If I remember correctly, Range was introduced in ONNX in opset 11 (the latest) and probably the onnx-coreml converter just hasn’t caught up yet (going based on the error message). If so, this is a gap in the converter. Please close this issue if the latest exported ONNX model works as expected in onnxruntume. Thanks.
